 performance tracking and audit compliance.  Sterling Electro India Pvt. Ltd. — India Client: RSPL | Project: Soda Ash Chemical Plant, Gujarat | Role: Electrical Supervisor | Duration: || Key Responsibilities: | Aug | 2017-2020 |  Additional Projects under Sterling Electro:  Led installation, testing, and commissioning of electrical systems, ensuring full compliance with safety and quality standards.  Executed installation of lighting systems, control panels, transformers, circuit breakers, and earthing systems with precision.  Conducted daily toolbox meetings, verified PPE compliance, and maintained a safe working environment on site.  Reviewed electrical drawings, cable schedules, and coordinated resources for smooth project execution.  Managed contractor teams, monitored progress, and prepared Daily Progress Reports (DPR) for management review.  Supervised preventive, predictive, corrective, and breakdown maintenance of electrical systems including motors, transformers, panels, and HVAC units.  Handled cable laying, glanding, termination, continuity testing, and panel wiring for instruments and electrical systems.  Coordinated with clients for technical discussions, approvals, and handover documentation to ensure project deliverables met all specifications.  Ensured strict adherence to safety standards, including PPE usage, work permits, barricading, scaffolding, and high-altitude safety procedures. Client: Amazon Warehouse, Pune (16 July 2021 – 30 Oct 2021): Key Responsibilities:  Supervised electrical installation, LV & ELV systems, and MEP equipment ensuring quality and safety compliance.  Planned daily work schedules, allocated tasks to contractors, and monitored manpower deployment.  Conducted site inspections, reviewed shop drawings, material submittals, and method statements.  Ensured PPE usage, site barricading, scaffolding/lift safety, and high-altitude work compliance.  Maintained billing, material records, attendance, and prepared Daily